This paper deals with contextual bandit algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on adversarial attacks on these algorithms, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). However, the paper also involves optimization and decision making (cs.LG), as well as algorithms and complexity (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with machine learning algorithms.
